{{Infobox university |image= <!-- Do NOT place a non-free image here without complying with WP:NFCC #10c --> |name=UWâMilwaukee College of Nursing |type = [[Public university|Public]] |established = |dean = Sally Lundeen |city =[[Milwaukee]] |state =[[Wisconsin]] |country =[[United States]] |campus =[[University of WisconsinâMilwaukee]] |phone= |website= [http://www4.uwm.edu/nursing http://www4.uwm.edu/nursing] |logo=<center>[[Image:UW-Milwaukee.png|150px]]</center> |}} The '''College of Nursing''' is a college within the '''[[University of WisconsinâMilwaukee]]'''. It is the largest nursing school in [[Wisconsin]], offering bachelor's, master's, and doctoral degrees.<ref>[http://www4.uwm.edu/nursing/about/dean_welcome.cfm http://www4.uwm.edu/nursing/about/dean_welcome.cfm]</ref> In addition to the main campus at [[UW-Milwaukee]], the College of Nursing also has a Bachelor of Science in Nursing Program at [[UW-Parkside]] and [[UW-Washington County]].<ref>[http://www4.uwm.edu/nursing/undergrad/bachelor/ Bachelor of Science in Nursing Program], UW-Milwaukee College of Nursing</ref>
The College of Nursing was ranked 32nd nationally by ''[[U.S. News & World Report]]'' in 2010.<ref>[http://grad-schools.usnews.rankingsandreviews.com/best-graduate-schools/top-nursing-schools/rankings/page+2 U.S. News & World Report Rankings - Nursing 2007]</ref> It ranked 36th among Schools of Nursing in the US for [[National Institutes of Health]] (NIH) funding.<ref>[http://www.brimr.org/NIH_Awards/2009/NIH_Awards_2009.htm Ranking Tables of NIH funding to Hospitals and Other Health Science Schools],</ref>
